sentences: Susannah McCorkle (January 1, 1946 – May 19, 2001) was an American jazz singer.
She began her career in the early 1970s by singing at pubs in London with bandleader John Chilton.
After moving back to the U.S. in the 1970s, she sang at the Cookery in Greenwich Village and the Riverboat in Manhattan.
No More Blues (1989), her first album for Concord Jazz, was recorded with guitarists Emily Remler and Bucky Pizzarelli and pianist Dave Frishberg.
Stereo Review magazine named How Do You Keep the Music Playing (1985) album of the year, while critic Leonard Feather named it vocal album of the year.
